item.description:

[quote=“qauters, post:6, topic:277559”][quote author=Unhandled link=topic=366436.msg2778139#msg2778139 date=1241639839]

[ Render Hack ]
	HIDDEN
	HIDDEN
	HIDDEN
	HIDDEN
	HIDDEN

Some proprietary information I see
[/quote]
Not that it’s some huge thing anyway :P. Render methods are renamed in Speljohans 503 deob (search this forum). Everything that needs rendering implements the following method:

public abstract void render(int i, int i_7_, int i_8_, int i_9_,
			int i_10_, int i_11_, int i_12_, int i_13_, long l);

So you simply rename that to _render and all implementations also get’s renamed.
Then you add a method:

public void render(int i, int i_7_, int i_8_, int i_9_,
			int i_10_, int i_11_, int i_12_, int i_13_, long l)
{
   if(Client.shouldRender())
   {
      _render(i, i_7_, i_8_, i_9_, i_10_, i_11_, i_12_, i_13_, l);
   }
}

Something in this direction should work just fine. Of course use the runescape name instead of render :P, _render can be anything you wish.
Don’t forget to parse the order of arguments etc, but since most of them are int’s it will be piss easy.

If I made some mistake, be so kind to tell me it ;)[/quote]why do something as ugly and stupid as that? why not just return
